 This program
 
 
 ;; Intermediate
 
 (require (lib "image.ss" "htdp"))
 
 
 (image-inside? (overlay (text "" 12 'red) (rectangle 100 100 'solid  
 'white))
                 (text "" 12 'red))
 
 causes an error:
 
 > (lib "image.ss" "htdp") broke the contract
 >   (->
 >    (-> (is-a?/c interface:dc<%>) any)
 >    (and/c integer? exact? (between/c 1 10000))
 >    (and/c integer? exact? (between/c 1 10000))
 >    (is-a?/c class:bitmap%))
 > on build-bitmap; expected <(and/c integer? exact? (between/c 1  
 > 10000))>, given: 0
 
  From my preliminary investigations, the error is triggered by  
 something inside of image-inside because each subexpression alone  
 evaluates just fine.
 
 -- Matthias
 
 
 
 
