 Possibly image-inside? assumes all non-empty images.
 
 I guess the right fix is to make image-inside? just return #t when
 given an empty image (as a special case).
 
 Thanks for checking into that. I suspect there might be other problems
 with zero-sized images. (Possibly: returning them at the REPL)
 
 Note taht Steve has long been asking for zero-sized images, so it
 might be worth trying to dig up the PRs that he submitted, while
 you're working on that.
 
 Or, if you want, you can hand this over to me now. I should have time
 today to get to it.
 
 Robby
 
